==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Anallagmatic
<hw>An`al*lag*mat"ic</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/;
<grk>'an</grk> priv. + <?/ a change.]</ety> <fld>(Math.)</fld> <def>Not
changed in form by inversion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Anallagmatic curves</b></col>, <cd>a class of curves of
the fourth degree which have certain peculiar relations to circles; --
sometimes called <altname>bicircular quartics</altname>.</cd> --
<col><b>Anallagmatic surfaces</b></col>, <cd>a certain class of surfaces
of the fourth degree.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Anallantoic</ent>⟦br⟧
